<a href="#0" id="0">The partner units problem is an acknowledged hard benchmark problem for the logic programming community with various industrial application fields like CCTV surveillance or railway safety systems.</a>
<a href="#1" id="1">Whereas many complexity results exist for the optimization version of the problem, complexity for the decision variant, which from a practical point of view is more important, is widely unknown.</a>
<a href="#2" id="2">In this article we show that the partner units decision problem is NP-complete in general and also for various subproblems of industrial importance.</a>
